        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Claiming Losses After Disasters Act</strong></p> <p>This bill revises the tax deduction for personal casualty losses arising from major federally-declared disasters. It replaces the current requirement that such losses exceed 10% of a disaster victim's adjusted gross income before a deduction can be claimed with a minimum threshold of $500 in losses per disaster.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
